---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
import { tools, verticals } from '../lib/data';
import useCasesData from '../data/use_cases.json';

const toolCount = tools.length;
const verticalCount = verticals.length;
const useCaseCount = (useCasesData.use_cases as unknown[]).length;
const verifiedDates = tools.map(t => t.pricing.verified_date).sort();
const oldestVerified = verifiedDates[0];
const newestVerified = verifiedDates[verifiedDates.length - 1];
---

<Layout
  title="About WrenchStack — The independent trades software directory"
  description="WrenchStack is the only fully independent, affiliate-funded directory comparing field service software for HVAC, plumbing, electrical, roofing, and other trades. Here's how it works and why it exists."
>
  <article class="mx-auto max-w-3xl px-4 py-12">

    <header class="mb-12">
      <p class="mb-3 text-sm font-semibold uppercase tracking-wider text-orange-600">About WrenchStack</p>
      <h1 class="text-4xl font-bold tracking-tight text-slate-900 md:text-5xl">
        The trades software directory we wished existed — so we built it.
      </h1>
      <p class="mt-6 text-xl text-slate-700 leading-relaxed">
        WrenchStack is an <strong>independent comparison directory</strong> for field service and trades software.
        We track {toolCount}+ platforms across {verticalCount} verticals, publish data-driven rankings,
        and earn affiliate commissions when readers sign up. <strong>Rankings are not for sale.</strong>
      </p>
    </header>

    <section class="mb-12 grid gap-4 sm:grid-cols-3">
      <div class="rounded-lg border border-slate-200 bg-white p-5 text-center">
        <div class="text-3xl font-bold text-slate-900">{toolCount}+</div>
        <div class="mt-1 text-sm text-slate-600">Software platforms tracked</div>
      </div>
      <div class="rounded-lg border border-slate-200 bg-white p-5 text-center">
        <div class="text-3xl font-bold text-slate-900">{verticalCount}</div>
        <div class="mt-1 text-sm text-slate-600">Trades verticals covered</div>
      </div>
      <div class="rounded-lg border border-slate-200 bg-white p-5 text-center">
        <div class="text-3xl font-bold text-slate-900">600+</div>
        <div class="mt-1 text-sm text-slate-600">Indexed comparison pages</div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="prose prose-slate max-w-none">

      <h2>Why this exists</h2>

      <p>
        Search "best HVAC software" right now. You'll land in one of three places, and all three fail
        the contractor making a real software decision:
      </p>

      <ol>
        <li>
          <strong>Vendor blogs masquerading as comparisons.</strong> Workyard's "best HVAC software"
          guide ranks Workyard at #1. ServiceTitan's "best for tradies" guide ranks ServiceTitan #1.
          FieldBoss's? Same. These aren't comparisons. They're sales pages with extra steps.
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Generic SaaS aggregators</strong> like Capterra and G2. Massive databases of every
          piece of business software ever made — 260+ products in just the HVAC category. No real
          guidance on which fits a 4-person plumbing shop vs a 30-tech commercial mechanical contractor.
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Content-mill articles.</strong> Five paragraphs of fluff, padding text, lists of
          tools without any pricing comparison, no head-to-head feature analysis. Written for SEO,
          not for the buyer.
        </li>
      </ol>

      <p>
        None of those help a contractor making a $5,000-$50,000-per-year software decision. So we built
        the resource we wished existed: <strong>independent, data-driven, brutally specific about
        which tool fits which business, and structurally optimized for the questions buyers actually ask.</strong>
      </p>

      <h2>What makes us different</h2>

      <table>
        <thead>
          <tr>
            <th></th>
            <th>WrenchStack</th>
            <th>Capterra / G2</th>
            <th>Vendor blogs</th>
          </tr>
        </thead>
        <tbody>
          <tr>
            <td><strong>Trades-only focus</strong></td>
            <td>✅</td>
            <td>❌ Generic SaaS</td>
            <td>⚠️ Single vendor</td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td><strong>Rankings independent of payouts</strong></td>
            <td>✅</td>
            <td>⚠️ "Sponsored" placements</td>
            <td>❌ Always #1</td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td><strong>Verified pricing with date stamps</strong></td>
            <td>✅</td>
            <td>⚠️ Often outdated</td>
            <td>❌ Usually hidden</td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td><strong>Head-to-head comparison pages</strong></td>
            <td>✅ ~480 pairs</td>
            <td>⚠️ Limited</td>
            <td>❌ Only vs self</td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td><strong>Specific buyer-guide pages</strong></td>
            <td>✅ ({useCaseCount} guides)</td>
            <td>⚠️ Generic</td>
            <td>❌ One use case</td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td><strong>No email gate to read</strong></td>
            <td>✅</td>
            <td>❌ Login required</td>
            <td>⚠️ Often gated</td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td><strong>Vendors review content before publish</strong></td>
            <td>❌ Never</td>
            <td>⚠️ Influence rankings</td>
            <td>✅ They wrote it</td>
          </tr>
        </tbody>
      </table>

      <h2>How we rank</h2>

      <p>
        Four equally-weighted factors. The ranking algorithm has <strong>zero knowledge</strong> of which
        tools we earn commissions from or how much they pay.
      </p>

      <ol>
        <li><strong>Aggregated user ratings</strong> — averaged G2 + Capterra scores</li>
        <li><strong>Pricing transparency</strong> — tools with public pricing rank above "contact sales" black boxes</li>
        <li><strong>Integration depth</strong> — QuickBooks, payment processors, marketing tools, industry-specific integrations</li>
        <li><strong>Feature coverage for declared use case</strong> — solo-contractor tools don't get penalized for lacking enterprise reporting; enterprise tools don't get praised for solo-friendly features they don't have</li>
      </ol>

      <p>
        Read the full ranking algorithm and audit trail on the <a href="/methodology/">methodology page</a>.
      </p>

      <h2>Editorial commitments — in writing</h2>

      <ul>
        <li>
          <strong>We do not accept paid placements.</strong> No vendor can buy a higher ranking, a
          "featured" badge, or sponsored content. Period.
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Vendors do not see drafts.</strong> Tools learn about our coverage of them when
          everyone else does — when it publishes.
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>We fact-check pricing quarterly.</strong> Every tier has a verified date.
          Pricing data on this site ranges from {oldestVerified} to {newestVerified}.
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>We publish criticism even of affiliate partners.</strong> When the data says a
          tool we earn no commission from is the right pick, we say so. ServiceTitan pays us up to
          $10,000 per signup, but if you're a solo contractor we'll still recommend Jobber.
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>We correct errors within 48 hours.</strong> Mistakes are noted on the page with a
          dated correction stamp — never silently edited.
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>We don't fabricate user reviews or testimonials.</strong> Direct user quotes, when
          we use them, are sourced from public reviews on G2, Capterra, or vendor case studies — never
          invented.
        </li>
      </ul>

      <h2>Who runs WrenchStack</h2>

      <p>
        Built and operated by <strong>Bilal Elhomsi</strong>, an entrepreneur with 15+ years of operating
        experience in business development, growth strategy, and consulting across hospitality, retail,
        and technology ventures. WrenchStack is a solo operation — every review, comparison, ranking,
        and buyer guide on this site is written by one independent operator, not a paid content team.
      </p>

      <p>
        That's intentional. Content teams optimize for word count and editorial calendar; one operator
        optimizes for being right.
      </p>

      <p>
        We're based in Saudi Arabia. Our editorial focus is the North American field service software
        market exclusively — that's where the most competitive product ecosystem exists, where most
        software dollars get spent, and where most of our readers buy.
      </p>

      <h2>How we make money</h2>

      <p>
        Affiliate commissions. When a contractor lands on WrenchStack, reads a comparison, and signs up
        to a software platform through one of our tracked links, the vendor pays us a referral fee
        (typically $50-$10,000 per signup depending on the platform).
      </p>

      <p>
        <strong>You pay nothing extra.</strong> The commission comes from the vendor's customer-acquisition
        budget — the same money they'd otherwise spend on Google Ads or sales reps. Buying through
        WrenchStack's link is the exact same price as buying direct, except some of the marketing budget
        flows to the people who helped you find the right tool.
      </p>

      <p>
        We are <strong>not</strong> funded by:
      </p>

      <ul>
        <li>Display advertising (no banners, no Google Ads on pages)</li>
        <li>Sponsored content (no "in partnership with" articles)</li>
        <li>Featured-tool placements (no "vendor of the month" sections)</li>
        <li>Lead-resale (we don't capture your email and sell it)</li>
        <li>Email gates (everything on the site is readable without signing up)</li>
      </ul>

      <p>
        We earn when our recommendations help. Read the full breakdown on the
        <a href="/disclosure/">affiliate disclosure</a> page.
      </p>

      <h2>What you'll find here</h2>

      <ul>
        <li><strong><a href="/tools/">{toolCount}+ tool reviews</a></strong> — every major field service platform, with verified pricing, feature lists, integrations, and weaknesses</li>
        <li><strong><a href="/compare/">~480 head-to-head comparisons</a></strong> — side-by-side breakdowns of any two tools that share a vertical</li>
        <li><strong>{verticalCount} vertical landing pages</strong> — best HVAC, plumbing, electrical, roofing, landscaping, cleaning, pest control, and more</li>
        <li><strong><a href="/best-software-for/">{useCaseCount} buyer guides</a></strong> — picks specific to solo contractors, growing teams, QuickBooks-heavy shops, insurance restoration roofers, snow-management landscapers, and other concrete buyer profiles</li>
        <li><strong><a href="/pricing/">Pricing comparison pages</a></strong> for every vertical — sorted cheapest first, every tier visible</li>
        <li><strong>Tool alternatives pages</strong> — when a specific tool doesn't fit, here's what does instead</li>
      </ul>

      <h2 id="contact">Contact</h2>

      <p>
        <strong>For corrections, vendor outreach, partnership inquiries, or media:</strong><br />
        <a href="mailto:bcrypto.eth@gmail.com">bcrypto.eth@gmail.com</a>
      </p>

      <p>
        If you're an affiliate program manager wanting to set up a partnership, please include in your
        first message: program name, commission structure, payout terms, and tracking platform
        (PartnerStack, Impact, direct, etc.).
      </p>

      <p>
        If you're a vendor and spot an error about your product on our site, email us — we'll fix it
        within 48 hours, no escalation needed. We don't need you to threaten to pull your affiliate
        program; accurate data benefits everyone.
      </p>

      <hr />

      <p class="text-sm text-slate-500">
        <strong>Site launched:</strong> May 2026<br />
        <strong>Most recent update:</strong> {new Date().toLocaleDateString('en-US', { year: 'numeric', month: 'long', day: 'numeric' })}<br />
        <strong>Pricing data verified:</strong> {oldestVerified} to {newestVerified}<br />
        <strong>Domain:</strong> wrenchstack.com (registered May 2026)
      </p>

    </section>
  </article>
</Layout>
